Dyspareunia. Tracing the cause.
 Difficult or painful sexual intercourse is a sensitive topic for most women.
 The causes range from inflammation of the vulva and interstitial cystitis to marital discord.
 To exclude an organic disorder, a detailed pelvic examination with good lighting and magnification is in order.
 Dr DeWitt describes the technique for meticulous examination and discusses the diagnoses that need to be considered.
